+# PR-214 Remediation Report
+
+## Thread Triage
+
+- `T-214-01`: actionable
+- `T-214-02`: duplicate of `T-214-01`
+- `T-214-03`: obsolete
+- `T-214-04`: actionable
+- `T-214-05`: actionable
+
+## Code Changes
+
+### `src/policy/approval_router.py`
+
+- Normalized `approval_state` inside `build_policy_preview(...)` before calling
+  `build_preview_payload(...)`.
+- This ensures `manual_review` is converted to
+  `human_review_required` for both live-preview and fallback-preview paths.
+
+### `src/policy/preview.py`
+
+- Preserved `approval_state` in the fallback
+  `status="preview_unavailable"` payload.
+- Added `requires_human_review` to the same fallback payload so the review
+  state remains visible when preview rendering is disabled.
+
+### `tests/test_preview.py`
+
+- Added a regression test covering
+  `build_policy_preview(request_id="req-214", approval_state="manual_review", preview_enabled=False, actor="review-bot")`.
+- The test verifies the fallback payload retains
+  `approval_state="human_review_required"` and
+  `requires_human_review=True`.
+
+### `docs/approval_policy.md`
+
+- Updated the fallback response example to match the corrected payload.
+- Removed the stale note claiming the fallback example still needed the reopened
+  thread to land.
+
+## Verification
+
+Executed:
+
+```bash
+python3 -m unittest tests.test_preview tests.test_approval_router
+```
+
+Result:
+
+- `5` tests ran
+- all passed
+
+## Reviewer Mapping
+
+- `T-214-01`: resolved by the router normalization plus fallback payload fix
+- `T-214-02`: classified duplicate; no separate code change
+- `T-214-03`: classified obsolete; suggestion intentionally not applied
+- `T-214-04`: resolved by the new fallback regression test
+- `T-214-05`: resolved by the corrected docs example
