## Review Reply Draft

### T-214-01

Fixed in `src/policy/preview.py` and `src/policy/approval_router.py`.
The fallback `preview_unavailable` payload now preserves `approval_state` and
`requires_human_review`, and the router now normalizes `manual_review` to
`human_review_required` before building the payload.

### T-214-02

No separate code change. This is a duplicate of `T-214-01`, and the same
fallback payload fix addresses both threads.

### T-214-03

Not applied. The suggestion is attached to an outdated hunk in
`src/policy/approval_router.py` and would reintroduce legacy behavior, so this
thread is being treated as obsolete on the current branch.

### T-214-04

Added a regression test in `tests/test_preview.py` that exercises
`build_policy_preview(..., preview_enabled=False, approval_state="manual_review", ...)`
and asserts the fallback payload keeps
`approval_state="human_review_required"` with
`requires_human_review=True`.

### T-214-05

Updated `docs/approval_policy.md` so the fallback response example now includes
`approval_state: "human_review_required"` and
`requires_human_review: true`.

